End Term Project
Comprehensive SRE Implementation for a Distributed Microservices System
1. Title
End-to-End Implementation of Site Reliability Engineering Practices in a Multi-Orchestrated
Microservices Infrastructure Using Docker Swarm, Kubernetes, Terraform, and Ansible
2. Abstract
This project presents a comprehensive implementation of Site Reliability Engineering (SRE)
principles applied to a distributed microservices-based system. The system integrates
containerization, multi-platform orchestration, monitoring, infrastructure provisioning,
configuration management, incident response, and capacity planning.
The architecture consists of more than five independent microservices deployed using both
Docker Swarm and Kubernetes to demonstrate comparative orchestration strategies.
Infrastructure provisioning is performed using Terraform, while system configuration and
deployment automation are managed using Ansible.
Observability is achieved through Prometheus and Grafana, enabling real-time monitoring and
alerting. A simulated incident is introduced to evaluate system resilience, followed by a
structured postmortem analysis. Additionally, automation mechanisms and capacity planning
strategies are implemented to enhance reliability and scalability.
This project demonstrates a full SRE lifecycle, including system setup, monitoring, incident
management, automation, and performance optimization.
3. Objectives
The primary objective of this project is to demonstrate the integration of SRE practices across
the entire system lifecycle.
Specific objectives include:
1. Designing and deploying a distributed microservices architecture (6+ services)
2. Implementing multi-orchestration using Docker Swarm and Kubernetes
3. Provisioning infrastructure using Terraform
4. Automating configuration and deployment using Ansible
5. Defining SLIs and SLOs
6. Implementing monitoring and alerting systems
7. Simulating and resolving production incidents
8. Conducting postmortem analysis
9. Implementing automation and capacity planning strategies
4. System Overview
The system is a scalable web-based microservices application designed for SRE demonstration.
Microservices (≥ 6) you can use any other services for example:
1. Authentication Service — user login and security
2. Product Service — product catalog management
3. Order Service — order processing
4. Payment Service — payment handling simulation
5. Notification Service — email/alert simulation
6. User Profile Service — user data management
Supporting Components
1. Frontend: Nginx-based web interface
2. Database: PostgreSQL
3. Optional Message Broker: Redis / RabbitMQ
4. Monitoring: Prometheus + Grafana
